$ Display manager [X]
@ display manager

A display manager is the first X program run if the system (as opposed to a → Linux/user) starts → Linux/X.

The display managers lets a user log in.


{ Implementations

  GDM (Gnome), KDM (deprecated), Xdm, LightDM, LXDM, SLiM (Simple Login Manager), SDDM, qingy etc.

}
{ Login manager

  *Login manager* is a synonym for display manager.

}

sa:

 `→ Linux/fhs/etc/X11/default-display-manager`

 `→ Linux/fhs/etc/systemd/system/display-manager_service`

 `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share/xsessions`

  Display the name and status of the active display manager service:
code {
→ Linux/init/systemd/tools/systemctl status display-manager
code }

  → Linux/X
